args: This made an even bigger fuss\nthan I expected.
Though I suppose their ruling lord\nDID just up and vanish...
He feared reprisal because he was fully\naware of how terrible his misrule was.
Probably shoulda tried being less of a\nvillainous crapsack. Anyway, now we gotta\ndecide what to do about the aftermath.
Thank you once again for all that\nyou have done for our town.

Guess the cat's out of the bag, huh?
Still, you shouldn't be thanking me for
running off and doing things without
talking to all of you first.
What I did ended up throwing\nyour town into chaos...
Yeah, bad as he was, a local official\ndisappearing like this is gonna lead\nto trouble down the road.
Sure, there might be trouble ahead—\nbut what would the kids say if a little thing\nlike THAT made us lose heart?
We were all ready to live under that lord's\nboot heel for the rest of our natural days,\nbut our children showed us another way.
They're tiny and inexperienced, but they\nstill found the courage to stand and fight.
And their courage helped us find our own.
Yep. If we don't stand tall now,\nwe'll never be able to face our children.
Sounds like this town is gonna be just fine.\nAfter all, you've got some pretty awesome\nguardians here!
We tried to stand up to the bad soldier,\nbut it just got our dads hurt.
It would've been better if we hadn't\ndone anything at all...
That's not true. You kids changed\nthe adults here precisely because\nyou were brave.
Heck, you changed the whole town!

Of course! Without you, they'd probably
still be running around polishing that
jerk's fancy boots and thinking they had
no other choice in the matter.
You gave them hope—you showed them\nthere was another way.
Honestly, you even showed me that.
You made me remember the courage\nit takes to stand and face things.
You... You mean it? Hee hee!
Mewheheh! THERE are those smiles!\nAnd with that, my work here is done.
You know you're welcome to stay here\nfor as long as you like, Mona.
That's right. Won't you stay here?\nOur sleepy town is so much more lively\nwith you in it!

Sorry, but the curtain's fallen on my time.
Besides, you've already got yourselves a
band of super-cool phantom thieves
watching over you!
He's gone. Aw, and we didn't even\nget a chance to thank him properly...
You sure you're good with us\npeacing out like that?
Then why do you look so bummed?
You coach budding new phantom thieves,\nMona? I had no idea.
How do you all know about...?\nWait, was this YOU, Luca?!
Guilty as charged. I mean, we DID\ncome here to set up a Jail heist, yeah?
Sorry, guys... I should have kept my\neyes on the ball, and instead I ran off\nand made a huge mess of everything.
And you were right to do it.
You'd get the same answer from the\nprince, too, so there's no need to be\nkeepin' any of this a secret.
But hey, the town's at peace, and the\nEmpire no longer has any eyes there.\nAll's well that ends well.
And that means our preliminaries are all\ntaken care of. Our operation's sure to\nbe a success now!
Now we just have to get the Desires\nout of Emile's Jail.
